  "doc_id": "14601",
  "text": "The main aim of naturalistic design used in this study was to measure physiological changes during day to day stress. Building up on 24 h continuous ECG measurement studies [CITATION_1] , naturalistic studies in salivary cortisol [CITATION_2] , and our laboratory studies, we chose to analyze shorter measurements of ECG which were repeated several times during one year. Due to this design, we could also address the question of within subject development in allergy, anxiety and control subjects. In our design, participants individually selected dates of stressful and relax days based on expected stressors in their lives, most of which were work related. We used various psychological measures, such as adjectives checklist, 10-point scales of subjective stress and also widely used PSS (perceived stress scale) to assess whether given measurements could be analyzed as stressful or relax measurements.",
